                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12783153" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 27 Nov 2009 19:25:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m currently working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1744&quot; title=&quot;Thrift server to match the new java api.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1744&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1744&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; so I thought about moving it to contrib at the same time. Got the build scripts etc. working already. Not very much to do.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve got two questions: The thrift-server is currently started with the hbase command line script. After this move it is not guaranteed to be available. My knowledge of shell scripts is very limited so I have no idea how to proceed. I could provide a thrift script to start/stop the server. What is the preferred way to go here?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And how does &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1476&quot; title=&quot;scaling compaction with multiple threads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1476&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1476&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; affect this move? I&apos;m not very familiar with the inner workings of HBase&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12783154" author="streamy" created="Fri, 27 Nov 2009 19:29:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see the connection with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1476&quot; title=&quot;scaling compaction with multiple threads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1476&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1476&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  I think I may have been the one to link the issues but used the wrong one.  Can remove the link if no one else speaks up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far &quot;guarantee&quot; of availability, as long as it&apos;s a separate script or options from all normal hbase stuff, and there&apos;s a descriptive message if thrift contrib is missing, then I don&apos;t see any issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12829433" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 4 Feb 2010 04:29:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stack does not want to do contrib for HBase any more. Thrift in particular is important to maintain, so we shall keep it in core. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
